{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"Root cause PROVEN + reproduced: a vanished loose object poisons the shared index; the failed whole-index commit leaves the entry staged, so every later write cascades (invalid object/Error building trees). Fix: _recover_from_invalid_object (read-tree HEAD + re-add + retry), wired into stage_and_commit + batch. Vetted — adversarial code review: APPROVE/ship; prior-art sweep: acceptable-with-caveats, all guardrails met (git-annex uses the identical index-rebuild). Added observability guardrail (WARN naming any orphaned worktree path) per both reviews. RED tests mutation-checked; lint/typecheck/full store suite (311) green; concurrency test green x4 locally. Pushed as Gerrit change 762. Non-blocking follow-up 9f8e: reconcile the orphaned worktree file."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784263869410757001,"uuid":"94d4b649-fca0-41b9-be2b-185c7cebe9e0"}